http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Welfare-initiative/article13998685.ece

The State government will provide vehicles for the Mandal Parishad Development Officers (MPDOs) in the coming 10 days, so that they can take the message of the government’s development ambitions to the people, Minister for Panchayat Raj and Rural Development K.T. Rama Rao announced here on Wednesday. Speaking after launching the diary of Telangana MPDOs’ Association, Mr. Rao urged the officers to work as bridge between government and people. He also promised towards promotions for them, which are long pending.